### 4. Dashboard Positional Parsing — `parseDashboardPositionalArgs` in `resolve.ts`

**Bug fix:** When 2 args are passed and the first is a bare slug (no `/`), `parseDashboardPositionalArgs` passes it through to `parseOrgProjectArg` which produces `project-search` mode, and `resolveOrgFromTarget` silently ignores it (falls through to auto-detect). Apply the same normalization as `parseDashboardListArgs`: if the target has no `/`, append `/` to treat it as an org slug.

```typescript
export function parseDashboardPositionalArgs(args: string[]): {
  dashboardRef: string;
  targetArg: string | undefined;
} {
  if (args.length === 0) {
    throw new ValidationError("Dashboard ID or title is required.", "dashboard");
  }
  if (args.length === 1) {
    return { dashboardRef: args[0], targetArg: undefined };
  }
  // Normalize bare org slug → org/ (dashboards are org-scoped)
  const target = args[0].includes("/") ? args[0] : `${args[0]}/`;
  return { dashboardRef: args[1], targetArg: target };
}
```

This fixes `sentry dashboard view my-org 'My Dashboard'`, `sentry dashboard widget add my-org ...`, etc.

